# sample  register  data
# Channel 0 at moderate operator levels for the algorithm/feedback
# perceptual scenarios. attack_all_carriers drives every operator at total
# level zero, and at that maximal modulation depth a four-stage cascade is
# chaotic: a fraction of a percent of table-quantization difference in one
# stage moves the next sine index by dozens of steps, so any two correct
# implementations with different table quantization diverge trajectory-wise
# and the spectral comparison measures chaos flavor instead of kernel
# correctness. Moderate modulator levels (6-9 dB down) keep every cascade
# in the regime where quantization differences stay small and the gate
# discriminates real pitch/depth/routing/envelope errors. Raw rows are
# M1 $40/$60/..., M2 $48/$68/..., C1 $50/$70/..., C2 $58/$78/...; an
# operator's role varies with the overridden algorithm, so the levels rise
# gently from M1 to C2 and the last slot stays prominent as the most
# common carrier.
0 20 c7
0 28 4c
0 30 00

0 40 01
0 48 01
0 50 01
0 58 01
0 60 08
0 68 0a
0 70 0c
0 78 02
0 80 1c
0 88 1c
0 90 1c
0 98 1c
0 a0 00
0 a8 00
0 b0 00
0 b8 00
0 c0 00
0 c8 00
0 d0 00
0 d8 00
0 e0 0f
0 e8 0f
0 f0 0f
0 f8 0f

# Key on all four operators on channel 0.
0 08 78
